    • Method Detail

      • defineAdditionalCommands

        public void defineAdditionalCommands()
        NOTE: This MUST be called after the field 'commandCodec' has been initialized. This method will define "additional commands" for this CommandExecutor.
        In HttpCommandExecutor, superHttpCommandExecutor.defineCommand(String, CommandInfo) will be called when executing 'newSession' (see HttpCommandExecutor.execute(org.openqa.selenium.remote.Command))
        When we reconnect to a session, we need to call this method so that the "additional commands" defined by CHROME_COMMAND_NAME_TO_URL will be recognized.

      • isRequired
